So I've definitely been seeing some recent changes in the search results during the last year. I've been sites that CLEARLY aren't optimized for SEO but are obviously written by first hand perspectives gaining traction in Google. 
This was probably the most glaring one. When doing research for our daughter's 4-year old car seat, I was looking up dimensions and stumbled across a site called "Car Seat For Littles". It had the exact dimensions that I needed for sizing the seat properly. 
However,  I was curious because it was ranking well. I wouldn't consider it super optimized site by SEO standards. However it DOES have: 
- A ton of unique imagery of the products
- It's clearly written by a person with SME-level knowledge of the seats
- It's structured well enough (headings/bullets) 
- Clear sense of community (doing a "Rafflecopter giveaway")
This isn't just a one-off either. I'm seeing definite trends of smaller sites that don't have traditional SEO performing better. This backs up a lot of the data Lily Ray has been posting. 
Will definitely be keeping an eye on this. 
